      "message": "No, no..what I head in mind was something like\n\n GET /v2.0/notification-methods\n\nreturns list of actual notification methods. Those entities, each one of them have a notification type that server (monasca-api) supports. My idea was to use OPTIONS http method over the same endpoint that could, as a response, return list of all possible types of notifications that server is capable of processing.\n\nIn other words that would something like\n\n OPTIONS /v2.0/notification-methods\n\n {\n   types: [\"WEBHOOK\", \"PAGERGUDY\", \"EMAIL\", \"JIRA\", \"HIPCHAT\"]\n }\n\nbut again, I think I might have overused what OPTIONS can be used for, so I guess that initial idea here is right way to go.\n\nBTW, sorry if that comment was out of place. I am still trying to figure this OPTIONS and I still come back in my mind to article I read while log - http://zacstewart.com/2012/04/14/http-options-method.html.\n\nThat\u0027s why I suggested that as an option to consider.",
